intro: Tarenna yunnanensis, commonly known as Yunnan tarenna, is a flowering plant native to China. It belongs to the Rubiaceae family, which includes over 13,000 species of flowering plants. The plant is characterized by its small, clustered flowers and elliptical leaves with a smooth surface. It typically grows in forested areas at moderate altitudes. Its botanical features make it of interest to botanists and horticulturists alike.
